      • processCommandHelp

        public void processCommandHelp(net.minecraft.command.ICommandSender icommandsender,
                               java.lang.String[] astring)
                        throws net.minecraft.command.CommandException
        This method is called when the user uses the command in an incorrect way. This command should either print out a friendly message explaining how to use the given (sub)command, or throw a CommandException with extra helpful information.
        Parameters:
        icommandsender - Use this commandsender to print chat message.
        astring - The list of strings that were entered as subcommands to the current command by the user.
        Throws:
        net.minecraft.command.CommandException - Thrown when the user entered something wrong, should contain some helpful information as to what wrong.
